        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:29PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Goldston, or 11 miles southeast of Siler City, moving north at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsboro and Goldston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
